==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Stound
<hw>Stound</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sudden, severe pain or
grief; peril; alarm.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Astonishment; amazement.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser. Gay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stound</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Stound
<hw>Stound</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>stund</ets>; akin to D.
<ets>stond</ets>, G. <ets>stunde</ets>, Icel. <ets>stund</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Hour; time; season.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A brief space of time; a moment.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>In a stound</b></col>, <cd>suddenly.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Chaucer.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stound</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Stound
<hw>Stound</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Stand</er>.]</ety> <def>A
vessel for holding small beer.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
